se.jguru.nazgul.core.quickstart.model

Class Name

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.jguru.nazgul.core.persistence.model.NazgulEntity
      • se.jguru.nazgul.core.quickstart.model.Name
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Name>, se.jguru.nazgul.tools.validation.api.Validatable

    @Entity
public class Name
extends NazgulEntity
implements Comparable<Name>
    Specification for how to build names for use within project structures. A name normally consists of up to three parts, on the form prefix-name-type (i.e. nazgul-foo-api-parent or similar). The order of the parts are as follows:
    1. prefix. An optional prefix for all names within a given project.
    2. name. A mandatory name.
    3. type. The type of name which may be used to indicate the functionality of the name, such as "api", "impl-jpa", "assembly" etc.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB
    See Also:

      • getStandardNullComparisonValue

        public static int getStandardNullComparisonValue(Object o1,
                                                 Object o2)
        Compares the two supplied objects, managing null and identity checks. The return value is found as follows:
        1. If both objects are null: 0
        2. If both objects are identical (o1 == o2): 0
        3. If o1 == null and o2 != null: -1
        4. If o1 != null and o2 == null: 1
        5. If neither o1 nor o2 is null: UNKNOWN
        0 if both objects are null or identical. 1 if o1 is not null and o2 is null, and -1 if o1 is null and o2 is not null. If both objects are non-null, UNKNOWN is returned.
        Parameters:
        o1 - The left hand object.
        o2 - The right hand object.
        Returns:
        0 if both objects are null or identical. 1 if o1 is not null and o2 is null, and -1 if o1 is null and o2 is not null. If both objects are non-null, UNKNOWN is returned.
